.sh NAME
pick \*- choose which arguments to send to standard output
.sh SYNOPSIS
pick ...
.sh DESCRIPTION
Pick prints each of its arguments in turn on the diagnostic output and
waits for a line to be typed on the user's teletype.
If the line starts with a 'y', the argument is copied to standard output.
If the line starts with an 'x', pick exits.
.ti+5
Pick is mainly useful in conjunction with args(I).
For example:
	pick * | args rm -f
.br
is equivalent to dsw(I).
.sh FILES
/dev/tty -- to read y's and x's from
